<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="notes-week-01">
  <title>Week 1:  January 12</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      This week begins with an exploration of systems of linear
      equations and the possibilities for sets of solutions.  Then we
      will develop an algorithm that transforms a system of equations
      into a form, called <term>reduced row echelon form</term>, that
      enables us to quickly draw conclusions about its set of
      solutions.
    </p>
  </introduction>

